Context: The Office of Academic Excellence is a department at George Brown College dedicated to advancing and improving programs. It is led by a team of experienced faculty and support staff. The office welcomes suggestions for new programs, which can be submitted via the website with answers to provided questions. Interested individuals can sign up to receive updates about application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, and tours. Contact information for the office includes a phone number (416-415-2000) and TTY number (1-877-515-5559), as well as an email address (ask.george@georgebrown.ca). The college's social media hub can also be visited for additional information. The content of the website is subject to change without notice and should not be considered a representation, offer or warranty. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
